Cp%3EAll%20I%20have%20ever%20wanted%20to%20do%20is%20work%20hard%20for%20a%20good%20future.%20I%20was%20born%20into%20and%20raised%20by%20people%20who%20struggled%20to%20set%20goals%20and%20provide%20for%20their%20kids%2C%20so%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20something%20better%20for%20my%20own%20when%20I%20decided%20to%20settle%20down.%20Unfortunately%2C%20to%20give%20my%20son%20the%20best%20future%20possible%2C%20I%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-advice-millionaire-no-plan-stocks-investing-staying-active-aging-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egive%20up%20any%20concept%20of%20retiring%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%2027%20when%20my%20partner%20and%20I%2C%20freshly%20married%2C%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdont-have-kids-but-help-my-friends-parent-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estart%20our%20family%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We'd%20done%20the%20entire%20checklist%20that%20we%20had%20been%20told%20would%20promise%20success.%20We%20both%20went%20to%20college%2C%20we%20got%20jobs%20in%20stable%20career%20fields%2C%20and%20built%20up%20savings%20and%20stability%20before%20getting%20married.%20By%202019%2C%20we%20felt%20ready%20to%20tie%20the%20knot%2C%20and%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20I%20was%20so%20baby%20hungry%20I%20already%20had%20a%20tote%20of%20little%20clothes%20tucked%20away%20in%20a%20bin%20in%20my%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%202019%20was%20a%20very%20different%20time.%20I%20was%20working%20in%20technology%20as%20a%20hardware%20specialist%20for%20a%20local%20school%20district%2C%20my%20partner%20was%20a%20teacher.%20Our%20rent%20was%20%241150%20for%20a%20three-bedroom%20house%20in%20a%20nice%20part%20of%20town.%20We%20were%20more%20than%20stable%2C%20very%20ready%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-own-my-house-and-my-partner-pays-me-rent-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuy%20a%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20conten