of%20Concorde%20001%20in%201969.%3Cp%3ERolls-Royce%20plc%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EConcorde%20001%2C%20with%20the%20tail%20number%20F-WTSS%2C%20was%20the%20first%20prototype%20built%20and%20made%20its%20first%20flight%20in%201969.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20retired%20to%20the%20museum%20four%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIt%20was%20a%20bit%20disappointing%20that%20the%20interior%20had%20been%20stripped%2C%20but%20there%20was%20still%20a%20lot%20to%20learn.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225712%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20inside%20the%20stripped-out%20Concorde%20001%20in%20Paris%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68766f2cf748d8c055f5a205%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EConcorde%20001%20was%20used%20to%20carry%20out%20scientific%20experiments%20during%20a%20total%20solar%20eclipse%20over%20Africa%20in%201973.%3Cp%3EPete%20Syme%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EInformation%20boards%20shared%20more%20about%20the%20history%20of%20this%20momentous%20airplane.%20For%20example%2C%20it%20was%20used%20to%20carry%20out%20scientific%20experiments%20during%20a%201973%20eclipse%2C%20with%20cameras%20and%20windows%20installed%20in%20the%20roof.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThere%20were%20several%20flight%20instruments%20behind%20glass%2C%20and%20a%20chance%20to%20glimpse%20the%20historic%20flight%20deck.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20cockpit%20on%20Concorde%20001%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68766f2c85e81483682e0821%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EConcorde's%20flight%20deck.%3Cp%3EPete%20Syme%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EConcorde%20was%20the%20first%20airliner%20to%20use%20fly-by-wire%20controls%2C%20which%20means%20electronic%20signals%20are%20sent%20to%20a%20computer%20that%20processes%20the%20pilots'%20inputs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20previously%20only%20used%20on%20military%20aircraft%2C%20but%20is%20commonplace%20today.%20The%20technology%20helped%20the%20A320%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbus-struggling-outsider-beating-boeing-737-max-a320neo-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAirbus's%20first%20major%20success%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConcorde's%20cockpit%20also%20included%20a%20third%20seat%20for%20a%20flight%20engineer%2C%20and%20controls%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bdroopsnoot%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lengthy%2C%20pointed%20nose.%20Used%20to%20add%20aerodynamic%20efficiency%2C%20the%20nose%20could%20be%20drooped%2010%C2%B0%20for%20more%20visibility%20during%20takeoff%20and%20landing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELeaving%20the%20first%20Concorde%2C%20it%20was%20great%20to%20see%20the%20original%20colorful%20livery%20with%20the%20names%20of%20the%20manufacturers.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225712%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20exterior%20of%20the%20first%20Concorde%20001%20prototype%20with%20the%20manufacturer's%20names%20painted%20on%20the%20side%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68766e3d85e81483682e0801%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20prototype%20was%20painted%20with%20the%20names%20of%20the%20French%20and%20British%20planemakers.%3Cp%3EPete%20Syme%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20British%20Aviation%20Corporation%20and%20France's%20Sud%20Aviation%20jointly%20built%20and%20developed%20Concorde.%20(Mergers%20and%20acquisitions%20over%20the%20years%20saw%20the%20former%20become%20part%20of%20BAE%20Systems%2C%20and%20the%20latter%20part%20of%20Airbus.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConcorde%20was%20a%20symbol%20not%20just%20of%20national%20pride%20for%20the%20UK%20and%20France%20but%20also%20of%20international%20cooperation%20between%20them.%20Indeed%2C%20the%20jet's%20name%20comes%20fro